  "text": "Despite these limitations, our results highlight the importance of taking into account the capacity for a reimbursement database to capture drugs. We believe that reimbursement databases, and in particular the Erasme database presented in this paper, are useful tools for pharmacoepidemiological research. Indeed, Erasme includes a large population and most of the drugs marketed in France. Thus, this database has been extensively used for 20 years for epidemiologic and pharmacoepidemiologic research [CITATION_1] . It is crucial to know the structure of a database, especially if it was not originally developed for pharmacoepidemiological research.",
